parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission issues can cause the vehicle to jerk, stall, or fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts harshly
the vehicle jerks or bucks
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle stalls or loses power
and the transmission warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dead Pedal or Throttle Response Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dead pedal or throttle response issues can cause the vehicle to fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when merging into traffic or crossing multiple lanes.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to accelerate when the accelerator pedal is depressed
there is a delay in throttle response
the vehicle hesitates or lags when accelerating
and the accelerator pedal feels unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The EGR cooler failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, and potentially causing a fire.
symptoms: The engine overheats
the coolant temperature gauge jumps rapidly
and the engine warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The SCR system failure can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to decreased performance and potentially causing a breakdown.
symptoms: The engine warning light illuminates
the exhaust regeneration system malfunctions
and the engine performance decreases.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fan shroud failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, and potentially causing a fire.
symptoms: The fan shroud tears or breaks apart
the engine overheats
and the engine warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repairs can cause the vehicle to remain in an unsafe condition, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The recall repair is delayed
the parts are unavailable
and the manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the track bar bracket can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates violently
especially at high speeds; the steering wheel pulls to one side; the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or shakes; the steering wheel pulls to one side; the vehicle is difficult to control; uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uneven tire wear can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Uneven tire wear; tires wear out quickly; vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Steering issues can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or vibrates; the vehicle is difficult to control; the steering wheel pulls to one side.
